name: Euribor
tagline: A very basic euribor graph in a web page
body:
### Welcome to Euribor graph
This is a small hack that i made because... well... because I wanted to see how was my mortage varing.

So, there you are. A very basic and simple webpage (all javascript) that plots the historic euribor rates (since 1999) up until today and optionally a target series to check if you how much you are fu^d^druined. :)

### Contributors
Please feel free to fork this repository and/or send pull requests of new things! :)

### Thanks to
* Banque de France for its data
http://www.banque-france.fr/economie-et-statistiques/changes-et-taux/les-taux-interbancaires.html
* Google for its charts
* Twitter bootstrap for its css
* Jquery for.. jquery! :)
note: Don't delete this file! It's used internally to help with page regeneration.
